la-library and com.typesafe:config transitively; the observed failure is caused by tests using deprecated classic TypedActor APIs that were removed in Pekko 2.0.0-M1, not by missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Do not use removed org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor, TypedActorExtension, or TypedProps APIs from the 1.1.5 tests. Cover the 2.0.0-M1 pekko-actor artifact through classic ActorSystem/Actor/Props, serialization, configuration, dispatchers, event stream, coordinated shutdown, or utility APIs. If a test intentionally exercises Java serialization, configure that ActorSystem with pekko.actor.allow-java-serialization=on and pekko.actor.warn-about-java-serializer-usage=off. If a test intentionally exercises DNS default-name-server internals, it may need the existing JVM/native --add-exports=java.base/sun.net.dns=ALL-UNNAMED flags; otherwise no global property is needed.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Pekko documentation recommends pekko-actor-typed for new typed-actor code, but that is a separate artifact and should not be added just to fix coverage for pekko-actor_2.13.\",\n    \"Pekko 2.0.0-M1 removes many deprecated APIs; generated tests should be based on classes present in the 2.0.0-M1 jar, not copied from the 1.1.5 test set.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0fd1f07c7e07741e016a411256ea388197a733f62308479688\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1765, "output": 900, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30825, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782649419820, "responseId": "resp_0fd1f07c7e07741e016a41124c50b48197a1081ba151d4625d"}, "toolResults": []}
